                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d556">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">893.00/12494: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Minister in China (<persName type="to">Johnson</persName>)</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1933-10-28T14:00:00-05:00"
                            >October 28, 1933—2 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>359. Your 819, October 28, 1 p.m., paragraph 3. In Department’s 358, October 27,
                    4 p.m., the phrase “officials of other governments” should be read to include
                    Chinese officials.</p>
                <p>You should endeavor in conversations with British officials to persuade them to
                    take the same position which you, acting under Department’s instruction as given
                    in 358, will take.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
